conclusion.electoral-propaganda-analysis: While this is clearly electoral propaganda, it is targeting the parliamentary elections (for deputy position) and not the presidential elections. The law in question (Article 55 t) specifically concerns presidential election propaganda after its conclusion. Since this advertisement is for a different election with an active campaign period, it does not constitute a violation.
